data.name: CreateSpheresHint
data.value:
Postprocess the lattice structure by editing the connections.
A solid sphere is created at all angled joints. The diameter of the solid sphere is a multiple of the largest bar diameter, which is adjacent to a specific connection joint.

data.name: PointMassManualHint
data.value:
Use Manual Point Mass to represent the effects of a component or mass not included in the simulation model. Such a component should have very little effect on the model stiffness.
After specifying the location on the model, specify its mass. Point masses are useful for reducing model complexity.

data.name: AngularGlobalLoadHint
data.value:
Use an angular body load to apply an angular velocity or angular acceleration to a part.
Select faces or edges to define the direction and location references of the applied load.

data.name: PointMassAutoHint
data.value:
Use Auto Point Mass to represent the effects of an existing component in the simulation model. This is useful for simplifying the simulation model.
To assign a point mass, select the geometric item on which the point mass acts.
